d%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20%E2%80%94%20the%20channel%20of%20a%20YouTuber%20who%20rose%20to%20fame%20at%20age%203%20unboxing%20toys%20on%20camera%20%E2%80%94%20have%20raked%20in%20as%20much%20as%20%2435%20million%20a%20year.%20In%20a%202023%20Morning%20Consult%20survey%2C%2057%25%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-influencer-marketing-career-goal-ai-social-media-instagram-2024-4%23%3A~%3Atext%3DMore%2520than%2520half%2520of%2520Gen%2C%2522%2520games%252C%2520and%2520explain%2520money.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cu%3EGen%20Z%20respondents%20said%20they%20wanted%20to%20be%20influencers%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20trend%20of%20kids%20playing%20influencer%20has%20gotten%20so%20unwieldy%20over%20the%20past%20two%20decades%20that%20lawmakers%20across%20the%20country%20are%20stepping%20in%20and%20attempting%20to%20regulate%20it.%20The%20trend%20started%20in%202023%2C%20and%20since%2C%20California%2C%20Utah%2C%20Minnesota%2C%20and%20Illinois%20have%20passed%20laws%20that%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fparenting-influencers-in-illinois-now-have-to-pay-children-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cu%3Emandate%20kids%20receive%20compensation%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20a%20trust%20if%20they%20appear%20in%20about%20one-third%20of%20someone's%20monetized%20content%20or%20if%20the%20poster%20hits%20a%20certain%20income%20threshold%20from%20their%20content.%20Some%20give%20the%20children%20the%20right%20to%20demand%20the%20content%20be%20deleted%20when%20they%20become%20adults.%20Half%20a%20dozen%20or%20so%20more%20states%20are%20drafting%20their%20own%20bills.%20It's%20a%20move%20that%20recognizes%20content%20creation%20as%20labor%20and%20not%20amateur%20home%20videos%20capturing%20kids%20being%20kids.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20laws%20are%20bolstered%20by%20the%20most%20heinous%20examples%20of%20parents%20abusing%20the%20children%20they%20force%20to%20perform%20in%20monetized%20videos.%20Shari%20Franke's%20recently%20published%20memoir%2C%20%26quot%3BThe%20House%20of%20My%20Mother%2C%26quot%3B%20is%20a%20look%20inside%20one%20of%20the%20most%20insidious%20cases%20of%20a%20parent%20exploiting%20children%20in%20a%20drive%20for%20online%20fame%2C%20one%20that%20involved%20abuse%20and%20the%20introduction%20of%20an%20abusive%20life%20coach%20into%20their%20family%20in%20Utah%20(her%20mother%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fruby-franke-now-child-abuse-jail%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cu%3ERuby%20Franke%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20is%20serving%20prison%20time%20for%20four%20counts%20of%20aggravated%20child%20abuse).%20Their%20family's%20story%20became%20a%20major%20driving%20force%20behind%20the%20Utah%20law%2C%20which%20is%20set%20to%20take%20effect%20in%20May.%20Some%20parents%20have%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2024%2F02%2F22%2Fus%2Finstagram-child-influencers.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cu%3Esold%20photos%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20of%20their%20children%20in%20revealing%20outfits%20to%20men%20online%2C%20running%20Instagram%20accounts%20for%20their%20young%20daughters.%20A%20new%20Netflix%20docuseries%2C%20%26quot%3BBad%20Influence%2C%26quot%3B%20alleges%20that%20the%20%26quot%3Bmomager%26quot%3B%20Tiffany%20Smith%20became%20verbally%20and%20physically%20abusive%20and%20forced%20preteens%20to%20work%20alongside%20her%20daughter%20for%20long%20hours%20to%20create%20YouTube%20content.%20(Some%20of%20the%20other%20former%20stars%20involved%20in%20the%20content%20settled%20a%20%241.85%20million%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpiper-rockelle-11-kids-sue-youtubers-mom-alleging-abuse-exploitation-2022-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cu%3Elawsuit%20with%20Smith%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20last%20year.%20Smith's%20daughter%2C%20Piper%20Rockelle%2C%20has%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.vanityfair.com%2Fhollywood%2Fstory%2Fnetflix-bad-influence-youtube-kid-influencers%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cu%3Edenied%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20the%20claims%20that%20her%20mother%20was%20abusive%2C%20and%20Smith%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpeople.com%2Ftiffany-smith-allegedly-encouraged-underage-daughter-piper-rockelles-stalker-by-sending-him-photos-in-exchange-for-gifts-11711126%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cu%3Esaid%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20the%20docuseries%20showed%20a%20%26quot%3Bfalse%20narrative.%26quot%3B)%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFor%20all%20the%20good%20intentions%20the%20laws%20bring%2C%20they%20lack%20teeth.%20There's%20no%20enforcing%20body%2C%20critics%20say%3A%20The%20kid-fluencers%20would%20need%20to%20first%20know%20the%20laws%20exist%20and%20then%20have%20the%20resources%20to%20sue%20for%20their%20money%20once%20they%20turn%2018%20if%20their%20parents%20didn't%20set%20up%20trusts.%20The%20laws%20require%20people%20to%20keep%20records%20of%20the%20content%20they%20created%2C%20compensation%20received%2C%20and%20what%20they%20deposited%20into%20accounts%20for%20their%20children.%20Even%20if%20there's%20recourse%20to%20sue%20your%20parents%2C%20it's%20likely%20to%20make%20coming%20home%20for%20the%20holidays%20more%20than%20awkward%2C%20and%20grown%20children%20of%20influencers%20may%20take%20these%20steps%20only%20in%20the%20most%20extreme%20circumstances.%20Even%20as%20the%20trend%20shows%20lawmakers%20want%20to%20do%20something%20about%20child%20influencers%2C%20they%20largely%20don't%20address%20questions%20about%20whether%20children%20can%20or%20should%20consent%20to%20spending%20hours%20in%20front%20of%20a%20ring%20light%20or%20unboxing%20toys.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20so%20tricky%20because%20on%20the%20one%20hand%2C%20these%20children%20are%20engaged%20in%20labor%20and%20deserve%20to%20be%20compensated%20for%20their%20labor%2C%26quot%3B%20Sara%20Petersen%2C%20the%20author%20of%20%26quot%3BMomfluenced%2C%26quot%3B%20tells%20me%20in%20an%20email.%20%26quot%3BBut%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20should%20these%20children%20be%20engaged%20in%20such%20labor%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPetersen%20says%20the%20laws%20could%20normalize%20child%20labor%20and%20pave%20the%20way%20for%20children%20to%20be%20seen%20as%20employees%20of%20their%20parents%2C%20which%20could%20lead%20to%20more%20harm.%20As%20natural%20as%20influencing%20may%20look%20to%20the%20viewer%2C%20Petersen%20says%2C%20it's%20really%20%26quot%3Bthe%20performance%20of%20a%20self%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20blurs%20the%20line%20between%20public%20and%20private%20aspects%20of%20life%2C%20even%20for%20adults.%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20think%20children%20are%20capable%20of%20the%20kind%20of%20psychological%20compartmentalization%20necessary%20in%20professional%20influencing%2C%20nor%20do%20I%20think%20they%20should%20be%20asked%20to%20be%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20adds.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIllinois%20was%20the%20first%20to%20pass%20such%20a%20law%2C%20which%20took%20effect%20in%20July%2C%20quickly%20followed%20by%20California.%20They%20take%20similar%20approaches%3A%20Content%20creators%20must%20set%20aside%20portions%20of%20earnings%20from%20content%20in%20which%20children%20appear%20and%20put%20it%20into%20a%20trust%20for%20when%20the%20kids%20turn%2018.%20They're%20modeled%20largely%20on%20the%20Coogan%20Law%2C%20which%20mandates%20child%20actors'%20employers%20keep%2015%25%20of%20the%20kids'%20income%20in%20a%20trust%20their%20parents%20can't%20touch%20(some%20of%20the%20state%20laws%20use%20this%2015%25%20figure%2C%20while%20others%20require%20more%20income%20to%20be%20set%20aside).%20Utah%20passed%20its%20own%20law%20in%20March%2C%20which%20stipulates%20children%20receive%20pay%20for%20the%20time%20they're%20featured%20if%20the%20accounts%20rake%20in%20more%20than%20%24150%2C000%20in%20a%20year.%20Utah%20has%20been%20a%20hub%20for%20mom%20influencers%20and%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrad-wives-have-exploded-in-popularity-since-roe-v-wade-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cu%3Etradwives%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20Women%20there%2C%20many%20of%20whom%20are%20members%20of%20The%20Church%20of%20Jesus%20Christ%20of%20Latter-day%20Saints%2C%20show%20an%20idealistic%20version%20of%20home%20life%20and%20traditional%20gender%20norms%2C%20sometimes%20as%20a%20way%20to%20subtly%20evangelize%20their%20faith%20online%2C%20but%20also%20to%20monetize%20their%20roles%20as%20homemakers.%20Now%20the%20state%20is%20pivoting%20toward%20regulating%20how%20children%20use%20and%20are%20seen%20on%20the%20internet%20%E2%80%94%20both%20with%20the%20new%20kid-fluencer%20protections%20and%20with%20a%20new%20ban%20on%20smartphones%20and%20smartwatches%20in%20schools.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20biggest%20swing%20among%20the%20laws%20comes%20from%20Minnesota%2C%20where%20children%20under%20the%20age%20of%2014%20won't%20be%20able%20to%20%26quot%3Bwork%26quot%3B%20in%20content%20come%20July.%20The%20new%20law%20there%20defines%20working%20as%20appearing%20in%20more%20than%2030%25%20of%20compensated%20content%3B%20if%20parents%20break%20this%20rule%2C%20children%20are%20entitled%20to%20sue%20for%20all%20the%20money%20made%20from%20the%20content.%20Those%2014%20and%20older%20who%20make%20their%20own%20content%20get%20to%20keep%20all%20the%20money%20under%20the%20law.%20The%20feasibility%20of%20the%20laws%20will%20be%20put%20to%20test%20in%20the%20courts%20if%20children%20grow%20up%20and%20do%20bring%20lawsuits%2C%20but%20Allison%20Fitzpatrick%2C%20a%20partner%20at%20the%20New%20York%20law%20firm%20Davis%2BGilbert%20who%20represents%20brands%20that%20hire%20influencers%2C%20says%20%26quot%3Bparents%20better%20start%20following%20these%20laws%2C%26quot%3B%20adding%3A%20%26quot%3BAt%20some%20point%2C%20their%20child%20can%20sue%20them%20if%20they%20do%20not%20take%20these%20steps.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finfluencer-economy-boomed-250b-industry-small-creators-feel-pushed-out-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cu%3EInfluencing%20has%20ballooned%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20the%20past%20decade%20and%20become%20a%20way%20to%20get%20work%20outside%20the%20traditional%20market.%20Before%20the%20last%20century%2C%20children%20always%20worked%20%E2%80%94%20first%20in%20agriculture%20or%20as%20apprentices%20to%20family%20businesses%2C%20and%20then%20in%20factories.%20Then%20we%20decided%20as%20a%20society%20that%20they%20shouldn't%20be%20clocking%20in%20and%20out.%20Aside%20from%20carve-outs%20for%20child%20actors%2C%20some%20top-tier%20athletes%2C%20and%20after-school%20gigs%2C%20the%20US%20mostly%20outlawed%20child%20labor.%20But%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20there's%20been%20a%20rise%20in%20states%20attempting%20to%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffair-labor-standards-act-hiring-child-laws-worker-shortage-iowa-minnesota-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cu%3Eroll%20back%20some%20child%20labor%20regulations%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20and%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbiden-administration-child-labor-crack-down-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cu%3Echild%20labor%20violations%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20have%20jumped.%20The%20proliferation%20of%20family%20influencers%20created%20a%20harder%20industry%20to%20regulate%20because%20so%20much%20of%20it%20takes%20place%20at%20home%2C%20in%20cars%2C%20or%20during%20daily%20life.%20%26quot%3BYou%20went%20to%20the%20factory%2C%20you%20went%20to%20the%20coal%20mine%2C%20and%20you%20got%20the%20kids%20out%20of%20there%2C%26quot%3B%20Hilary%20C.%20Robinson%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20law%20and%20sociology%20at%20Northeastern%20University%2C%20says%20of%20past%20child%20labor%20crises.%20Now%20%26quot%3Bwork%20is%20kind%20of%20everywhere%20and%20nowhere%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says%2C%20adding%3A%20%26quot%3BAnybody%20with%20a%20device%20has%20already%20been%20experiencing%20that%20since%20the%20era%20of%20the%20smartphone.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere%20are%20shocking%20stories%20of%20exploitation%2C%20but%20most%20families%20don't%20have%20anything%20close%20to%20a%20horror%20story%20unfolding%20out%20of%20frame.%20There%20are%20kids%20and%20teens%20who%20want%20to%20express%20themselves%20online%20and%20have%20broken%20through%2C%20connecting%20to%20their%20peers%20in%20huge%20ways.%20There%20are%20others%20pushed%20by%20their%20parents%20to%20do%20so.%20%26quot%3BIt%20is%20difficult%20for%20any%20brand%2C%20or%20for%20any%20agency%2C%20to%20really%20understand%20what%20goes%20on%20in%20the%20four%20walls%20of%20a%20family%20home%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Nick%20Walters%2C%20the%20president%20of%20SuperAwesome%2C%20a%20firm%20that%20represents%20brands%20and%20child%20influencers.%20Walters%20says%20his%20firm%20stays%20in%20close%20contact%20with%20families%20and%20will%20sever%20ties%20with%20those%20who%20don't%20put%20children's%20best%20interests%20first%2C%20perhaps%20by%20prioritizing%20content%20creation%20over%20schoolwork.%20He%20says%20he%20largely%20doesn't%20see%20the%20regulations%20as%20a%20hit%20to%20the%20influencer%20business%3A%20%26quot%3BSensible%2C%20common-sense%20regulation%20that%20recognizes%20that%20young%20people%20are%20going%20to%20be%20in%20these%20spaces%2C%20and%20make%20sure%20they%20are%20dealt%20with%20fairly%20and%20responsibly%20and%20in%20a%20way%20that%20is%20in%20their%20best%20interest%20%E2%80%94%20we%20are%20a%20huge%20supporter%20of%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEven%20as%20more%20people%20question%20whether%20and%20how%20children%2C%20or%20even%20themselves%2C%20should%20appear%20online%2C%20there's%20a%20massive%20demand%20for%20family%20vlogging%20content.%20People%20simply%20can't%20look%20away.%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20see%20these%20laws%20stopping%20the%20momentum%20that%20has%20taken%20place%20in%20the%20industry%20with%20respect%20to%20child%20influencers%2C%26quot%3B%20Fitzpatrick%20says.%20Some%20of%20the%20viewers%20are%20fans%2C%20but%20some%20are%20rage-watching.%20After%20several%20big-name%20influencer%20families%20moved%20out%20of%20California%20in%20quick%20succession%2C%20viral%20rumors%20circulated%20on%20social%20media%20that%20they%20were%20fleeing%20to%20avoid%20the%20state's%20new%20law%20in%20February.%20It%20was%20largely%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rollingstone.com%2Fculture%2Fculture-features%2Ffamily-vlogger-influencer-california-tennessee-move-1235282524%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cu%3Ehoax%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20Rolling%20Stone%20reported%20at%20the%20time%3B%20some%20influencer%20families%20had%20left%20California%20but%20did%20so%20for%20personal%20reasons.%20%26quot%3BTikTokers'%20outrage%20at%20parenting%20influencers%20isn't%20actually%20about%20protecting%20children%20or%20ethics%20in%20content%20creation%2C%20it's%20about%20pushing%20a%20moral%20panic%20for%20clicks%20and%20views%20%E2%80%94%20ironically%20the%20exact%20thing%20that%20they%20criticize%20influencers%20for%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20tech%20journalist%20Taylor%20Lorenz%20wrote%20recently%20in%20her%20newsletter%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.usermag.co%2Fp%2Fno-family-vloggers-are-not-fleeing-california-over-a-child-labor-law-viral-tiktok-false%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cu%3EUser%20Mag%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAll%20this%20regulation%20is%20focused%20on%20the%20concept%20that%20influencing%20is%20labor%20and%20the%20kids%20doing%20the%20work%20deserve%20a%20slice%20of%20the%20pie.%20There%20are%20still%20questions%20for%20all%20of%20us%20to%20answer%20about%20how%20children%20appear%20online%2C%20and%20what%20can%20be%20done%20to%20protect%20their%20privacy.%20In%20Europe%2C%20there%20are%20stronger%20protections%2C%20like%20the%20%26quot%3Bright%20to%20be%20forgotten%2C%26quot%3B%20that%20allow%20people%20to%20demand%20their%20images%20and%20data%20be%20removed%20from%20platforms%20(France%20passed%20a%20child%20influencer%20law%20in%202020%2C%20becoming%20a%20global%20pioneer%20in%20regulating%20the%20hours%20kid-fluencers%20worked%20and%20what%20happened%20to%20their%20compensation%20and%20enshrining%20a%20right%20for%20them%20to%20demand%20the%20deletion%20of%20videos%20they%20appear%20in).%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFor%20now%2C%20most%20Americans%20don't%20have%20those%20privacy%20luxuries%20against%20Big%20Tech.%20These%20laws%20are%20one%20of%20the%20first%20steps%20in%20recognizing%20that%20people%20are%20going%20to%20post.%20If%20they're%20lucky%20enough%20to%20strike%20gold%2C%20at%20least%20the%20kids%20propelling%20them%20to%20the%20top%20will%20see%20a%20cut.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Famanda-hoover%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3EAmanda%20Hoover%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20correspondent%20at%20Business%20Insider%20covering%20the%20tech%20industry.%20She%20writes%20about%20the%20biggest%20tech%20companies%20and%20trends.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href